<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ISO-8859-1" ?><grammar><title>Question tags</title><bgcolour>FFFFFF</bgcolour><darkcolour>3300cc</darkcolour><section><title>Question tags</title><sectiontitle>Use question tags to check information and to keep the conversation going.  To make question tags, repeat the auxiliary verb, not the main verb. Affirmative statements use a negative tag.  </sectiontitle><titlesound>Interm_Gram_4_1_1.mp3</titlesound><text1>You can swim.</text1><sound1>Interm_Gram_4_1_2.mp3</sound1><text1a>You can swim, &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;can't you?&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text1a><text2>She has been here.</text2><sound2>Interm_Gram_4_1_3.mp3</sound2><text2a>She has been here, &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;hasn't she?&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text2a><titlesound2>Interm_Gram_4_1_4.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>Negative statements use an affirmative tag. Use negative statements if you think the answer to the question is 'No'.</sectiontitle2><text3>You don't live here.</text3><sound3>Interm_Gram_4_1_5.mp3</sound3><text3a>You &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;don't&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; live here, &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;do you?&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text3a><text4>We haven't received the tickets yet.</text4><sound4>Interm_Gram_4_1_6.mp3</sound4><text4a>We &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;haven't&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; received the tickets yet, &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;have we&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;? </text4a></section><section><title>Question tags</title><sectiontitle>If there is no auxiliary verb, use &lt;I&gt;do, does, did&lt;/I&gt; or their negatives.</sectiontitle><titlesound>Interm_Gram_4_1_7.mp3</titlesound><text1>She likes apples.</text1><sound1>Interm_Gram_4_1_8.mp3</sound1><text1a>She &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;likes&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; apples, &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;doesn't she?&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text1a><text2>They went to Paris.</text2><sound2>Interm_Gram_4_1_9.mp3</sound2><text2a>They &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;went&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; to Paris, &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;didn't they?&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text2a><titlesound2>Interm_Gram_4_1_10.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>If the main verb is &lt;I&gt;to be&lt;/I&gt;, repeat that.</sectiontitle2><text3>You are from Egypt.</text3><sound3>Interm_Gram_4_1_11.mp3</sound3><text3a>You &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;are&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; from Egypt, &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;aren't you&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;?</text3a><text4>I'm not on the list.</text4><sound4>Interm_Gram_4_1_12.mp3</sound4><text4a>I&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;'m not&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; on the list, &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;am I?&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text4a></section><section><title>Short answers</title><sectiontitle>For short answers use the auxiliary verb.</sectiontitle><titlesound>Interm_Gram_4_1_13.mp3</titlesound><text1>He doesn't like cats, does he?</text1><sound1>Interm_Gram_4_1_14.mp3</sound1><text1a>No, he &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;doesn't.&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text1a><text2>They are American, aren't they?</text2><sound2>Interm_Gram_4_1_15.mp3</sound2><text2a>Yes, they &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;are.&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text2a><titlesound2>%undefined</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>%undefined</sectiontitle2><text3>%undefined</text3><sound3>%undefined</sound3><text3a>%undefined</text3a><text4>%undefined</text4><sound4>%undefined</sound4><text4a>%undefined</text4a></section></grammar>